        " can do. Computer vision is concerned with the automatic extraction, analysis and understanding of useful information from a single image or a sequence of images. It involves the development of a theoretical and algorithmic basis to achieve automatic visual understanding.  The British Machine Vision Association and Society for Pattern Recognition Retrieved February 20, 2017 As a ": null
