    },
    {
        "human visual system": "Human Visual System"
    },
    {
        ", as a stepping stone to endowing robots with intelligent behavior. In 1966, it was believed that this could be achieved through a summer project, by attaching a camera to a computer and having it describe what it saw .     What distinguished computer vision from the prevalent field of ": null
    },
    {
        "digital image processing": "Digital Image Processing"
    },
    {
