        ".   Tracking and counting organisms in the biological sciences        Each of the application areas described above employ a range of computer vision tasks; more or less well-defined measurement problems or processing problems, which can be solved using a variety of methods. Some examples of typical computer vision tasks are presented below.     Computer vision tasks include methods for ": null
